## Button

**Path**: `@/components/Button`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → Button-mini (295:3020), Button-extra small (604:10317), Button-small (295:2939), Button-medium (82:993), Button-larger (10:116).

Text button with optional leading/trailing icon. **Sizes**: mini (24px height, caption, 4px radius), extraSmall / small (32px, paragraph-sm, pill), medium (body-md, pill), large (56px, body-lg, pill). **Variants**: default (filled slate-900), subtle (slate-100 bg), outline (1px border), transparent. **States**: hover, focus (2px border), disabled (grey-200, grey-700); mini subtle has active (blue-100 bg, blue-900 text).

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | Yes | Button label |
| `size` | `ButtonSize` | No | `"mini"` \| `"extraSmall"` \| `"small"` \| `"medium"` \| `"large"` (default `"medium"`) |
| `variant` | `ButtonVariant` | No | `"default"` \| `"subtle"` \| `"outline"` \| `"transparent"` (default `"default"`) |
| `leadingIcon` | `MaterialSymbol` | No | Leading icon name |
| `trailingIcon` | `MaterialSymbol` | No | Trailing icon name |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | Disabled state |
| `active` | `boolean` | No | Mini subtle: active/pressed state (blue tint) |
| `onClick` | `() => void` | No | Click handler |
| `type` | `"button"` \| `"submit"` | No | Button type (default `"button"`) |
| `aria-label` | `string` | No | Accessible name |
| `className` | `string` | No | Root class |

**Exports**: `Button`, `ButtonProps`, `ButtonSize`, `ButtonVariant`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/Button";

<Button onClick={() => {}}>Sign Up</Button>
<Button variant="subtle" size="small" trailingIcon="chevron_right">Next</Button>
<Button size="mini" variant="subtle" leadingIcon="school" active>Sign Up</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="large" disabled>Submit</Button>
```

