## Checkbox

**Path**: `@/components/Checkbox`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → checkbox (184:967), checkbox-items (505:2158).

24×24 box, 4px radius, 2px border. Optional **label**: row layout, 12px gap, medium/body-md; label colors: default slate-900, hover slate-950, disabled grey-700, error red-700. **Unchecked**: default (white, slate-400 border), hover (slate-200, slate-500), focus (slate-100, slate-900), disabled (grey-200, slate-200), error (red-100, red-400). **Checked**: same states with slate-100 bg (or grey-200 / red-100 when disabled/error) and check icon (slate-900, or grey-700 / red-700 when disabled/error). Supports controlled (`checked` + `onChange`) or uncontrolled (`defaultChecked`).

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `checked` | `boolean` | No | Controlled checked state |
| `onChange` | `(checked: boolean) => void` | No | Called when checked changes |
| `defaultChecked` | `boolean` | No | Initial checked when uncontrolled |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | Disabled state |
| `error` | `boolean` | No | Error state (red border/bg) |
| `label` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Label next to box (12px gap, medium/body-md) |
| `id` | `string` | No | Input id for form/label association |
| `name` | `string` | No | Input name for forms |
| `aria-label` | `string` | No | Accessible name (when no `label`) |
| `className` | `string` | No | Root label class |

**Exports**: `Checkbox`, `CheckboxProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { Checkbox } from "@/components/Checkbox";

<Checkbox label="Soft Plastic" onChange={(c) => setAccepted(c)} />
<Checkbox label="Accept terms" checked={value} onChange={setValue} />
<Checkbox aria-label="Accept terms" onChange={(c) => setAccepted(c)} />
<Checkbox defaultChecked disabled label="Disabled" />
<Checkbox checked error label="Error" />
```

