## Drawer

**Path**: `@/components/Drawer`

Slide-in panel with overlay for filters, settings, or secondary content. Renders in a portal. White panel, slate-200 border on inner edge, theme spacing (padding 24px). Optional header with title (medium/body-lg) and close IconButton. Closes on Escape, backdrop click (optional), or close button. Panel slides in from left or right with transition.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | When true, drawer and overlay are visible |
| `onClose` | `() => void` | Yes | Called when drawer should close |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | Yes | Panel content |
| `title` | `string` | No | Optional title in header with close button |
| `side` | `DrawerSide` | No | `"left"` \| `"right"` (default `"right"`) |
| `width` | `number` | No | Panel width in px (default 320, max 100vw) |
| `closeOnBackdropClick` | `boolean` | No | Close when clicking backdrop (default true) |
| `aria-label` | `string` | No | Accessible label when no title |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the panel |

**Exports**: `Drawer`, `DrawerProps`, `DrawerSide`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { Drawer } from "@/components/Drawer";

const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

<Drawer open={open} onClose={() => setOpen(false)} title="Filters">
  <p>Filter content here.</p>
</Drawer>
<Drawer open={open} onClose={() => setOpen(false)} side="left" aria-label="Menu">
  <nav>...</nav>
</Drawer>
```

