## DrawerTopBar

**Path**: `@/components/DrawerTopBar`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → Drawer-navebar (node 322:5273).

Header bar for use at the top of a drawer: back button (40×40, subtle), center title (semi/body-md, grey-900), optional action button (small, subtle). Padding 16px 24px, bottom border 1px slate-200, top corners rounded 34px. Use as first child of `Drawer` content; pass `className="-mx-6 -mt-4"` so the bar spans full width when the drawer content has default padding.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `title` | `string` | Yes | Center title |
| `onBack` | `() => void` | Yes | Called when back is pressed |
| `actionLabel` | `string` | No | Right-side action button label (e.g. "Add group") |
| `onAction` | `() => void` | No | Called when action button is pressed |
| `actionIcon` | `MaterialSymbol` | No | Optional icon for action button |
| `backAriaLabel` | `string` | No | Accessible name for back button (default "Back") |
| `className` | `string` | No | Root class (use `-mx-6 -mt-4` when inside Drawer) |

**Exports**: `DrawerTopBar`, `DrawerTopBarProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { Drawer } from "@/components/Drawer";
import { DrawerTopBar } from "@/components/DrawerTopBar";

<Drawer open={open} onClose={() => setOpen(false)} aria-label="Variants">
