## TrackInventoryCard

**Path**: `@/components/TrackInventoryCard`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → Track Inventory card (node 77:1368).

Card for tracking product inventory: header (title, subtitle, optional action link with chevron) and content (inventory rows with progress bars). **Empty** (`items` = []): one row “Empty” / “--” with empty progress bar. **Single** (one item): one row with large progress bar (full width). **Multiple** (2+ items): 2-column grid, each item has small progress bar (183px). Card: white, border-bottom 1px #E2E8F0, padding 48px 24px, gap 24px, max-width 440px. Title medium 24px #121412; subtitle body 16px #1E201E; action link medium 16px #101828 + chevron_right 16px. Row: name + detail (semi paragraph-sm), progress bar 16px (track slate-100, fill slate-900).

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `title` | `string` | No | Card title (default "Track Inventory") |
| `subtitle` | `string` | No | Subtitle (default "Monitor stock in one place") |
| `actionLabel` | `string` | No | Action link label (e.g. "Sign Up"); omit to hide |
| `onAction` | `() => void` | No | When action link is clicked |
| `items` | `TrackInventoryItem[]` | Yes | Each: `name`, `detail`, `progress` (0–1). Empty = empty state |
| `className` | `string` | No | Root class |

**Exports**: `TrackInventoryCard`, `TrackInventoryCardProps`, `TrackInventoryItem`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { TrackInventoryCard } from "@/components/TrackInventoryCard";

<TrackInventoryCard actionLabel="Sign Up" onAction={() => {}} items={[]} />
<TrackInventoryCard
  actionLabel="Sign Up"
  onAction={() => {}}
  items={[{ name: "Wobble Grub", detail: "100 sold / 500 amount", progress: 0.58 }]}
/>
<TrackInventoryCard
  actionLabel="Sign Up"
  onAction={() => {}}
  items={[
    { name: "Wobble Grub", detail: "100 sold / 500 amount", progress: 0.74 },
    { name: "Wobble Grub", detail: "100 sold / 500 amount", progress: 0.58 },
  ]}
/>
```

