## MediaDropzone

**Path**: `@/components/MediaDropzone`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → Image zone (node 87:1090).

Drop/click zone for images and videos. Default: white bg, 1px border #99A1AF, padding 24px, min-height 265px. Content: add_photo_alternate icon (42×42) + title (medium/body-lg 20px) + subtitle (medium/paragraph-sm 14px). **Hover**: bg slate-200, border slate-500. **Focus**: 2px border #101828. **Error**: bg red-100, border red-300, red text.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `title` | `string` | No | Main line (default "Select images ") |
| `subtitle` | `string` | No | Helper (default "You can only add up to 10 images / videos") |
| `onFilesSelect` | `(files: File[]) => void` | No | Called with selected/dropped files |
| `accept` | `string` | No | File input accept (default "image/*,video/*") |
| `maxFiles` | `number` | No | Max files (default 10) |
| `error` | `boolean` | No | Error state |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | Disabled state |
| `className` | `string` | No | Root class |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | No | When set, replaces placeholder (e.g. preview) |

**Exports**: `MediaDropzone`, `MediaDropzoneProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { MediaDropzone } from "@/components/MediaDropzone";

<MediaDropzone
  onFilesSelect={(files) => setFiles(files)}
